title: Introduction to SimpleITK
location: NIH Main Campus, Building 12, Room B51
description: The session will introduce participants to SimpleITK, a simplified programming interface to the algorithms and data structures of the Insight Segmentation and Registration Toolkit (ITK). This hands-on session will utilize Python based SimpleITK Jupyter notebooks to explore and experiment with various toolkit features. Participants will follow along using their personal laptops, enabling them to explore the effects of changes and settings not covered by the instructor.
